Engineering company Fluor Corporation has announced that Bill Langenbach has been named as the company’s new GM for South Africa. Langenbach has more than three decades of experience with Fluor, and has held various positions within the company and worked on a variety of projects. Until recently, he headed up operations for Fluor’s South African office. “I look forward to continue building Fluor’s presence in Africa as we offer comprehensive services to clients in diverse industries across the region,” Langenbach commented. Fluor is celebrating its sixtieth anniversary in Africa this year.